ну всяко лучше быдл с пивасами на уровне животных, которые пашут в диктатуре ради базовых физических потребностей таких как секс. ну и алкоголь, чтобы русскую тоску накрыть (вайб который с хрущевок в которых они живут). ловушка нищеты, и поделом вам, если первостепенно не духовенство, а низменные потребности. эпоха дворянства была нормальной только в россии, когда еще классики процветали, но и там было куча кутежов, а то что воспевали эти самые классики были лишь идиллическими образами (ну за исключением светского петербурга). И при Сталине было хорошо, в железных рукавицах держал этот народ, ну мы и видим как развивалась ссср - а сейчас что? сплошное разочарование и бесконечный цикл кредитов у 140 лямов. видите ли бухнуть и секса они хотят, уверен многие если даже не большинства рукоблуды (еще и дзюбу поливают грязью, жалкие), так как чтобы дала женщина нужно еще и заслужить, а рабы дофамина не многие могут, вот и накачивают гигабайтобороты порнхаба (глянь статистику посещения по сайтам, вероятно там немалые цифры, учитывая насколько Грей знают 90-е и нулевые, когда вся эта вертикаль власти и построилась)

text:
Les tiro un par de goles que no pueden faltar para la recopilación del 2022, los que se me vienen ahora a la mente:
1. El primero de Francia Inglaterra, de tchuameni (1-0)
2. El de Lionel Messi contra México (1-0)
3. El segundo de Camerún vs Serbia (3-2)
4. El tercero de Serbia vs Camerún (3-1)
5. Segundo gol de Mbappé en la final (2-2)
6. El gol de Angel Di María en la final (2-0)
7. El primer gol de Irán vs Gales (1-0)
8. El primer gol de Brasil vs Serbia (1-0)
9. El primer gol de Julián Alvarez vs Croacia (2-0)
10. Segundo gol de Japón a España (2-1)

Perdón si se nota mucho la argentinidad, no me puse a investigar, son los primeros 10 goles que me acuerdo ahora mismo jaja. De hecho si me dejan saco el de Camerún y pongo el golazo de Enzo Fernández a Mexico tambien (2-0)

text: За политику и коррупцию в этой ситуации ничего не скажу, но боже правый, как же горит с токсиков, которые пишут "бэки в отличие от неё постарались", "да она вообще не пела" а то и просто оскорбляют человека за якобы никчемное выступление. Во первых то, как неестественно для остального динамического диапазона песни выделяются бэки - явный косяк звукорежиссёра - у них громкость тупо выкручена в потолок, даже относительно инструментала. Вероятно это вообще сделано специально, так как в припеве Юлия тут вообще не поёт: логично предположить что такое наверняка не было задумано изначально, возможно у неё возникли сложности с исполнением этого припева на момент выступления (дыхалка начала сбоить например) и команда решила заглушить это орущими бэками, так как если бы она была в целом по жизни неспособна исполнять этот припев то наверное и песню сделали бы другой, где припев был бы не такой разрывной, но она бы вывозила. Да даже если и эту песню брать: если она в целом не вытягивает данный припев, это можно было бы грамотно обыграть: сделать бэки тише (что в любом случае необходимо, это же бэки) и дать ей параллельную партию по её силам, как в общем то и сделали в конце песни, только вот опять же, забыли приглушить бэки. Бэки эти молодцы, я не спорю, колоритно спели, но в композиции их роль - поддерживать основную линию, а не заглушать всё живое на сцене (что, повторюсь, не их косяк, а тех кто выставлял звук). Во вторых, ребят, ну серьезно, в куплетах Юлия поёт, и поёт нормально. Да, не прям космически, в силу её дыхательных ограничений, но у неё поставлен голос, она отыгрывает эмоции, она попадает в ноты, а это всё очень непросто, этому всему учатся, и учатся годами, по себе знаю, сам сейчас учусь в музыкальном колледже. Петь песни не так просто, как кажется с первого взгляда. Те, кто говорят что она дно - попробуйте записать как вы поёте под свою любимую песню, включив эту песню в наушниках, чтобы она не заглушала ваш голос на записи, и если вы не учились в музыкальной школе, вы ужаснётесь с результата, вот где вы услышите настоящее вокальное дно, я гарантирую это. Так что посыл такой: люди, будьте добрее, и если в чём то конкретном не разбираетесь, не судите так, будто вы профессионал. Это выступление – далеко не позорище. Да, есть минусы, и они во многом критичны для конкурса такого масштаба. Но по этим минусам вопросы скорее к композитору и продюссерам со звукарями, тот вокал что здесь есть - объективно не скрежет ножа по стеклу, видно что девушка искренне старается как может,  какая бы там продажная или политическая история за этим всем не стояла. Всем пис.

text:
I totally agree. The song's actually a pretty solid earworm and, whilst Samoylova is far from the strongest singer on earth, she doesn't go massively wrong anywhere in this song either. Aside from missing one of her lines at 2:02 (which the backing singers carry instead), all the notes she sings are what they should be.

It's the staging that ruined it for them. It would have worked so much better if they simply had her at the front of the stage with her wheelchair visible and the dancers and backing singers on either side behind her. Instead, they awkwardly perched her on top of a fake mountain towards the back of the stage, her wheelchair barely in view, with the dancers at the front distracting everyone from focusing at her.

text:
For me this was best world cup ever.
Fact that in final we had Croatia that was so underrated and unpredictable is enough.
Fact that Germany failed to progress in round of 16 and continued champions curse is enough.
We saw great comebacks and penalty shootouts.
Who believed that England will make it into semifinals???
Who believed that best player of tournament will be Luka Modric.
Who believed that Russia will progress into round of 16 and then eliminate Spain.
And I was pretty sad because all African teams were out before round of 16 but at least Morocco Senegal and Nigeria deserved to be there.
Iran was also so close but in the end so far from last 16.
For me just organisation was amazing.
Weather was nice troughout whole tournament.
Thank you Russia and all other nations for best world cup ever!!!

text: As a fan I do have some opinions: 1. I am overall disappointed with Fifa's decision to cancel the Confederations Cup in 2021. While I don't have anything against a new format for the Fifa Club World Cup I am against the 4 year format which will make that competition irrelevant and lose meaning since club teams sell and change their players often in the market and it would not really represent who is the real best club team in the world. 2. Fifa's decision to keep the Olympics for the men's game as a under 23 amateur contest is also disappointing. Why can't the men have the senior teams compete like in the Fifa World Cup? The Olympics would become the 2nd most important competition behind the World Cup since it would just field 16 teams. 3. I don't have anything against having 48 teams in a Fifa World Cup, but I am not so sure if they are ready to do that for 2022, maybe they should do it in 2026 to give the organizers time to prepare for a larger tournament. 4. While it is great to see that Fifa has the Fifa's Best award, they should just combine the Fifa world player of the year, fifa's best and Ballon d'or as one award all together in the future. It was a mistake for Fifa not to renew the contract for the Ballon d'or. 5. The World Cup hosting format should follow the continent rotation format. Oceania has never hosted the World Cup why? 6. VAR is a great thing for the sport, and I would love to see a Golden goal, Silver Goal and Bronze goal come into play. With a 3rd extra special time being the first five minutes worth a golden goal to win the game, the other five minutes worth 2 goals a silver goal, and the last 5 worth a Bronze goal which is just worth one goal to avoid Penalty kicks. 7. I haven't seen a  woman's Fifa Club World Cup yet and why is that? Fifa needs to do more to develop the women's division world wide which is highly behind the world famous and rich men's division for both national team and club team level.

text:
I'm sorry but this world cup was not that great for me. It was very entertaining but it was way off balance. France deserved to win the world cup and they were clearly the favorites but it was too easy for their side. Argentina was trash imo and without Messi they are nothing. Portugal, the same and they been like this for a decade already. Russia, Sweden, and Mexico were the countries that prevented Spain and Germany from advancing. Germany and Spain are not the same teams from 2010 and 2014 but they had more potential than what they show in the tournament. The fact that they had internal problems made it easier for them to fail. Let's face it as soon as we got into quarterfinals. We well knew that the champions was going to come from France, Brazil or Belgium. Croatia was fantastic team but their defense and forwards were not as great as Belgium, France and Brazil. Uruguay was a defensive team but in order for them to be dangerous you needed Suarez and Cavanni together. France played against an incomplete Uruguay. Netherlands, Italy, and Chile missing this world cup made it easier for countries like France and Belgium to advance faster. Netherlands, Italy and Chile probably wouldn't have won the world cup but they would have been tougher opponents than Sweden or Denmark. The fact that you have England and Russia advancing showed how lame this world cup was going to be. England was advancing thanks to Harry Kane scoring penalties. England has better team in 2006 and 2002 despite not going far than this team in 2018. Its great for the fans that Russia and England advance but eventually would have ran out. Should have England advance to the final. I'm pretty sure England would have lost just as badly as Croatia did. Maybe even more. England was lucky to beat a Colombia without James Rodriguez. France, Brazil, German, Spain, and Belgium were the only countries that were able to afford a player getting injured. The fact that Germany and Spain were taking out in the group stages made the world cup off balance. I mean sure it was great seeing Japan, Russia, England play wonderful but that didn't mean they were going to win the world cup.

France could have played better too. They played better when the opponent team had the ball. Grizeman and Mbappe were great counter attacks and Giroud despite not scoring was able to hold the ball so that Griezman and Mbappe could move forward. Argentina and France was a great match but Argentina played better the problem was that they had a garbage defense. The final against Croatia was controversial with that penalty and even that free kick. It affects a team psychological when they are down. Now it is true that France was a better team than Croatia but who knows what would happen if the ref didn't gave that penalty or free kick. Just look how awful France played in the group stages. France impress me against Belgium I give you that but other than that. I didn't really see France playing to their potential.

France 🇫🇷 
FIFA World Cup 2018

Group stage
🇫🇷 France 2-1 Australia 🇦🇺 (W)

🇩🇰 Denmark 0-0 France 🇫🇷 (D)

Round of 16
🇫🇷 France 4-3 Argentina 🇦🇷 (W)

Quarter-finals
🇺🇾 Uruguay 0-2 France 🇫🇷 (W)

Semi-finals
🇫🇷 France 1-0 Belgium 🇧🇪 (W)

Final
🇫🇷 France 4-2 Croatia 🇭🇷 (W)

Croatia 🇭🇷 
FIFA World Cup 2018

Group stage

text: Ferrari have won at two power circuits, but only just. Singapore is a strange one, nothing really similar on the calendar to compare data to. I think Mercedes will be stronger by a small margin, but I think it's all going to be down to tyre management and strategy from now on, they're both so close.
author: @Niko-xz5lk

text: @@Niko-xz5lk no they seemed to have a lot of downforce now and kept the straight line speed as well. Sochi should be easy for them as well.
author: @herebyhereby2874

text: @@herebyhereby2874 Yes, they certainly have made improvements to down force, but remember that there is no other track quite like Singapore and Ferrari set their car up there for qualifying pace as apposed to race trim. This was smart as Ferrari figured they could sacrifice race performance as it is very difficult to pass there. It csn also be said that Mercedes not only would have had better race pace at Singapore, but better tyre management too. None of these factors really came into play at Singapore, so Ferrari capitalised on those. Another point is that Mercedes made a bad strategy call and could have just as easily wond the race if they had used the undercut. You combine these factors along with a performance update package which I agree clearly showed improvement in the corners and you get the result we saw. As Toto and even Mattia have said,  Ferrari have not found a 'silver bullet' that will give them what they lack to Mercedes, but I do agree Ferrari are getting closer. I could be wrong, but I think Mercedes will have the edge at Sochi even with long straights.

text:
I'm go to back 4yrs ago. Remember 2018 football moment. Me and my sibling watched all match, we still watched start to end. The time was so beautiful. In our country our team mean Argentina always plays  football at 1:00-2:30 am something. So it was hard to watch as mummy dosen't permitted us to watch and It was our exam month so we get tierd to watch it at night and next morning go to school for exams. We had lots of struggle for watch football on 2018.  And ya that time jaundice occurred in my body. I was very very sick. But still I watched football. I can Remember one day purely, my body result was so hard and difficult. So family members, friends, cousins, were crying for me. But we were watching England vs Argentina match. And we were cried when our team mean Argentina lost in that match. That time it was sad. But now it’s golden time for us really. We were play a interesting game that was we were chat as footballers, We enjoyed most that time. Can't forget the golden time. I wanna go on 2018, but it’s not possible 😔

Love from Bangladesh 🇧🇩

text:
One man shouldered the burden of a whole nation, took them to almost all tournaments single handed and they betrayed him in Qatar when he needed the team to fight for him, the coach turned his back on him, team mates turned on him and the press… Ooh, Fifas tools always looking to down cast a man who came from nothing to be the BEST IN THE WORLD. They robbed him of the ballon d’or in the same year for fear of overtaking their favorite media son messi and instead gave it to Modric who didn’t even win the World Cup (at least they said it was a World Cup year). I already had my reservations about Fifa and their awards in 2010 when Messi won it and officially dismissed it in 2018. 
Thank you LEGEND RONALDO for everything, all the sweet memories and beautiful goals I will never forget especially the one against Juve in the UCL which had Even rival fans clapping. These deluded Messi fans can call u all d names they like tapnaldo, crynaldo, boxnaldo, penaldo and what other names, they know the truth you are one of the most skillful player to ever play the game, they know the truth you have more outside the penalty goals than their goat, they know the truth you have more solo goals than their goat, they know the truth you have more goals with ur weak left foot than their goat has with his right foot, you have more headers, you have more acrobatic goals, and you have more thunderbolts than their goat and yes it pains them to accept… you have more total GOALS than their goat both at club level and national level, at 38 man is still doing things nobody expected but at 36 their guy is the pink boys team and choking opponents anyhow these days 😂😂😂

CRISTIANO RONALDO, the BEST THERE EVER WILL BE

author: @youtpfpm6097

text:
@@youtpfpm6097 
Non tu as mal compris. De nombreux joueurs africains nés et élevés en Afrique n'ont pas reçu l'éducation des académies de jeunesse modernes. Et les académies de jeunesse modernes sont en Europe. C'est pourquoi Riyad Mahrez, Nabil Bentalebet Yacine Brahimi sont si bons : il est né et a grandi en France (mais ils jouent pour l'Algérie).
Lors de la dernière coupe du monde, presque tous les joueurs tunisiens sont nés en France. Aussi d'autres pays africains ont de bons joueurs qui sont nés en France. Les meilleurs joueurs africains qui jouent pour les équipes africaines ont reçu une formation dans les académies européennes de la jeunesse.
Les joueurs africains qui sont nés en Afrique et qui sont très bons sont très rares (par exemple Sadio Mané).
Alors c'est pour ça que notre pays est bon : nous avons colonisé l'afrique et donc les africains viennent ici. Et la grande majorité des Africains qui sont bons et qui jouent pour l'Afrique sont nés dans des pays comme la France.
Grâce à notre colonisation nous avons appauvri l'Afrique (mais c'est bien pour nous, on a leurs meilleurs joueurs).

text:
Today is the first time after the finale I had the guts to look at the game again. That day I was so heartbroken (I am Croatian, obviously) that even before the end of the game, I got out of the bar where I was watching the game with my friends. I went for an hour-long walk to chill myself, like a walking Forrest Gump. I never even wanted to look again at the game.. until today.

But we celebrated the whole night in Zagreb. It was so crazy, like we won the World cup! We were proud of the team and Croatia. I even ended up in a German tv sports show filming in the city. An amazing day I will never forget

text:
fun fact: the world cup winner's captain to lift the trophy since 2006 all have been goal keepers
2006-Italy (Buffon)
2010-Spain (Casillas)
2014-Germany (Neur)
2018-France (Lloris)

And another fun fact: the previous winners of the tournament to return the trophy in the finals since 2006 have all been defenders
2006- previous winner Brazil and player to return the trophy in 2006 final was Cafu,  position played- defender
2010- previous winner Italy and player to return the trophy in 2010 was Cannavaro, position played-defender
2014- previous winner Spain and player to return the trophy in 2014 final was Puyol, position played-defender
2018- previous winner Germany and player to return trophy in 2018 final was Lahm, position played-defender

Edit: And every 2006 and up world cup winners all have been European teams

text:
फुटबाल में चार साल में एक टूर्नामेन्ट होता है उसी चार साल में एक बार ही सबका मैच होता है जैसे क़ी अर्जेनटीना और ब्राजील का होता है इनकी कोई तीन मैच क़ी सीरीज नहीं होती है हर च्छे महीने में क्रिकेट क़ी तरह आपस में सभी देशो क़ी
फुटबाल का चार साल में एक टाइम एक मैच एक टूर्नामेंट होता है और पीर उसका ज्यादा क्रेज होता है अब क्रिकेट में हर एक दो साल में icc टूर्नामेंट होते रहते है और अब क्रिकेट में icc इंटरनेशनल मान्यता से 105 देश हो चूके क्रिकेट को खेलने बाले और फुटबाल 90 मिनिट गेम होता है और 90 मिनिट में क्या लगता है 500 करोड़ भी देख सकते है अब क्रिकेट का वल्ड कप 8 घंटे का एक मैच होता है पीर भी 160 करोड़ बता रहा है यह दर्शक संख्या देखने क़ी जबकि 160 करोड़ नहीं 310 करोड़ लोगो ने 2019 क्रिकेट वल्ड को देखा था गूगल सर्च कर लेना क्रिकेट में टाइम ज्यादा है तीन फॉर्मेट है हर महीने सीरीज होती रहती है लेकिन पीर भी दुनिया का दूसरा सबसे बड़ा स्पोर्ट है क्रिकेट को भी फुटबाल क़ी तरह एक टाइम एक  टूर्नामेंट एक फॉर्मेट का हो सभी टीम चार साल में एक बार भिड़े तो क्रिकेट का क्रेज भी दो गुना ज्यादा होगा फुटबाल से नंबर वन स्पोर्ट होगा दुनिया का

text: Imagine being 12 year old boy, living in a small country and obsessed with football and watching your country going to final on a World cup. And it was so dramatical, every game. I was having 7 heart attacks per game. But it was best summer ever, it was so unbelievable. The whole country was on fire. You couldn't see anyone on the street that's not in croatia jersey, even the tourists. I remember mandzukic's goal like it was yesterday and it is probably the best moment of my childhood. I jumped and run out of house screaming. My brother broke the vase, my mom who don't really like football cried because of joy and stress and relief, and I have never seen my dad that crazy. I will never forget it

text:
Its wierd how people have wrong perception of things. Noone remembers (or knows) nowdays that Croatia was acctualy slight favorite in this game according to bookmakers. It was something like 2.40 on Croatia and 2.60 on England. (in perspective in quarter finals 2022 against Brazil it was 1.30 on Brazil and 8.5 on Croatia).

 So many legends in this team. Almost every single player is his team captain. Every one of them is leader in big clubs. From 2010 to 2025 Croatia always had a player who won champions league. That is sick stat. 

I remember b4 this game someone made analysis and it was something like 5 or 6 Croatia players that had single more tropheys more than whole England squad. On a scale of whole team it was joke to compare. Non the less, Gareth Southgate did a fkn great great job with what he had to do. It was such a young talented team with no expirience and with the weight of whole nations expecations on their back. Plus that Gareth needed to do something very very hard. He had to change Englands football DNA. Bcs in modern football if he did not do it they would end up like Italy. But he crushed that task.

text: I wasn't even sad we lost to be honest with you. That summer was amazing, every single day was baking hot and the mood and atmosphere around the country was fever pitch, and we made it all the way to the Semi Finals and beat our penalty curse, which was almost like winning the World Cup for us (you will understand why if you're English.) Most of us didn't expect to get out of the group, let alone to the Semi Final, after going out to Iceland in 2016 England was at rock bottom and nobody had any belief in the team anymore. People had started giving up since Euro 2012 but that game against Iceland took a hammer to our morale. If we can get to the Semi Final of Euro 2020 this year I'll be more than happy with that. And if we hammer Scotland all the better.

this video just showed Paris, I live in a small town and believe it was just as hyped
this was everywhere in France
there were big screens that were bought just for the occasion (even in smaller town like I said) so that everybody could watch it together (and that from the quarter of finals to the finals)

even my 90-year-old great grand mother, who probably knows nothing about football, watched the games from her apartment and had flags on her balcony and watched as everyone was partying in the street below her
this was an actual nation celebration, that's what I mean, not just those who cared about football

That's just a different name at that point.
author: @KenanLaudat-tp3bp

text:
@@KenanLaudat-tp3bp That's what Wikipedia says...

"Association Football" (the actual name of the sport) was shortened by "Assoc -er" ("soccer").

It's a British shortened term...
author: @davepazz580

text:
​@davepazz580  I wasn't saying that wasn't the name. I was just confused about how you could get soccer from association football.
It makes more sense now, but it's still a bit confusing.
author: @KenanLaudat-tp3bp

text:
@@KenanLaudat-tp3bp From what I recall, there was a trend in Britain to shorten some words by adding an "-er" at the end of some words... so "breakfast" became "breakker".

So they took the "Association" and isolated the "socc" and added the "er" and it became soccer.

Funny thing is if you go back and watch some old British programs from the 60's or before then, they will say "soccer" when referring to the game.

The World = “Football”
* British: football (foot-ball)
* German: der Fußball (dehr foos-bahl)
* Dutch: het voetbal (het voot-bahl)

* French: le football (luh foot-bal), le foot (luh foot)
* Ukrainian: футбол (fut-bol)
* Swedish: fotboll (fot-bohl)
* Norwegian: fotball (fot-bal)
* Turkish: futbol (foot-bal)
* Russian: футбол (foot-bal)
* European Portuguese: o futebol (oh fut-bol)
* Brazilian Portuguese: o futebol (oh foo-tche-bol)
* Esperanto: futbalo (foot-ba-loh)
* Hindi: फुटबॉल (foot-bawl)

text:
Did you know that the term "soccer" was invented in the UK at the English public schools. They used to shorten "Rugby Football" to Rugger (a play on the word Rugby) and "Association Football" to "Soccer", which is a play on the word "association".

So if you don't like the term "Soccer" don't blame the Americans, blame the English.

text: This World Cup won't change anything in relation to the Messi vs Ronaldo debate, unless either one wins it & that ain't happening... Back the 2014 World Cup, the roles where reversed in the opening group games...Messi was scoring & playing really well & getting Argentina to the knock out stages, while Ronaldo struggled & Portugal got eliminated in the group stages...This World Cup it's the reverse. Ronaldo scoring & Messi struggling , with Argentina facing elimination at the group stages... Ultimately, people are gonna have their favorite player & who they consider the GOAT... There isn't a scientific objective measuring scale to prove once & for all, who is the GOAT...That's why before the millennium, it was ongoing between Pele & Maradona fans as to who, was the GOAT  & also, Di Stefano & Cruyff was in that discussion... Since 2000, Messi & Ronaldo have been added to that discussion...Like i said, there isn't an "objective" scientific method to decide this... It's like saying, who's the greatest between;The Beatles, James Brown, Jimi Hendrix, The Rolling Stones, Pink Floyd, Led Zeppelin, Stevie Wonder, Bob Marley, Michael Jackson, Prince... It's ultimately, all subjective.

text: Rigged isn't the right word, and you shouldn't only take this match to claim such things. But look at the whole tournament. We have to be honest here; Argentina did get more decisions in their favor than other teams. Was it rigged? No, but it could have been influenced. Take Qatar; how did they get the World Cup in the first place? We all know how... so would it be that strange if they tried to "push" Argentina for the win? Especially if you knew beforehand it would probably be Messi's last chance to win it. The thing with football is, it's not a sport with clear-cut rules.  A lot of times, it's how the referee and VAR interpret the situation. So, sadly, football, in my eyes, will never be a completely fair sport. We have all seen really shady decisions that left us with irritated feelings, or however you react to them. Not even talking about Argentina alone, but about the sport as a whole. Anyway, do I think it was rigged? No, but I wouldn't be surprised if they tried to push for Argentina to win.

text: The most aerodynamic thing is a teardrop, the spherical ball is definitely not very aerodynamic. The issues with it relate to the fact that the drag and flows behind the ball are less turbulent than those of its predecessors, because there are less seams and it has a smoother surface it’s both quicker through the air and it’s stability is less predictable. Its direction is harder to judge because the airflow can detach with an unpredictable outcome. It’s counterintuitive that a rough and less perfect ball is easier to control and to predict but ‘perfect’ airflow is very quick to become unbalanced but messy airflow that’s slower to change is easier for players to deal with.

text:
I hear a lot of people pointing out that Dafran is this and Dafran is that and that's why he shouldn't be community leader. But I Disagree. Dafran has experienced all aspects of high level play, giving him valuable experience to share with the Denmark team, way more than a mid gold player could ever give. Saying he would not make a good leader without even giving him a chance at ever being one Is pretty stupid if you ask me, considering all he has to offer. Giving community leader to someone who has no community and questionable leadership skills is also stupid. All she did was slander Dafran to further her chances at winning, that's not someone I would want as my leader. If you say you don't have to be good at he game to be a community leader you're wrong. Look at Jake, everyone thought he did a really good job casting in the Overwatch world cup. Do you think he would have done as good a job without his game sense and experience? The answer is HELL NO.   
At the end of the day, Dafran has done stupid things like abusing game mechanics to re spawn faster, but this doesn't show that he is a bad leader, it shows he either cares or doesn't care about ladder games, and if he doesn't care about ONE ladder game who cares. He said on stream he would try his best if he was chosen and that he was sorry for the stupid trolly things he has done. The pros of having him as a coach and community leader over a gold mercy main greatly outweigh the cons.

text:
I think this is all dumb and pointless.  Replay or not people will differ on any subjective call.  Is it offsides or not, are they in front or not, was that a hand ball or a kick off a hand in a "natural" position.  It doesn't matter if there is replay or not, you'll agree or you won't.  I think the suggestions of having some communication between some official and the on site and television fans is fine.  Same goes for replay in NFL, MLB, NBA, NHL, etc.  I don't think we should be able to "listen in" but I think they should have a statement explaining why the call was upheld/overruled.

But all this argument about right vs wrong in this video really has nothing to do with replay or not.

text: pavard should have won the award. imagine a youngster than very few have heard of, scoring a goal like that in a World Cup final. most players, even attackers would have at least took a touch of the ball before attempting the shot, or even passing it to players. but the sheer confidence and skill it took for him to not only score a beautiful volley, but to also gamble his chances in a World Cup final.
author: @ashrafzhuan8984

text: don't get me wrong, we saw some amazing goals from McGee, Ronaldo etc (except salah), but its not the goal itself for pavard. It was the intensity and the environment that he was in that made the goal extraordinary. In the back of his head when the ball was driving into the top bins he must've thought, "if I miss I'll not only embarrass myself, but my nation. I might even get subbed off", but he when the goal hit the back of the net, it was a moment of pure relief for him, and a moment of shock for the whole footballing nation. Obviously, many have performed like him in similar environment, like aguero's 93rd minute goal, or even mbappe's carry in the 2022's World Cup. But in 2018, without a doubt that was a goal that deserved to win the puskas.

text: For me, the three best goals that year were the ones scored by Bale, Ronaldo and McGree. If it is only about aesthetics, Ronado's is the best in my opinion, he lifts the foot way higher than Bale, with the leg is completely straight and vertical, and the ball leaves the foot with more power. Is true that Bale's is in a UCL final, so that is also something to have in mind, but I think this award is more about aesthetics. McGree's is more "incredible" or "unique", as it is an scorpion goal, but my only problem is that it wasn't scored on a big stage and I think it has that vibe of being a bit of a lucky goal, I am not so sure that his intention was to shoot (unlike Giroud's Puskas Award, with his scorpion, where it's perfectly clear that he was intending to score). So in my opinion, 1st is Ronaldo's, 2nd McGree's, and 3rd Bale's. Salah's is easily the worst one, he has scored way better looking goals than that one.
